content:
I woke up this morning with the story I covered yesterday still on my mind.
Two beautiful sisters celebrating the younger ones' 21st birthday-- tragically hit by a suspected drunk driver.
Vanessa Raghubar died at Jamaica Hospital Monday. Maria Raghubar is still there fighting for her life.
Both brilliant and beautiful and the kind of daughters and sisters anyone would cherish.
I spent some time with their grieving family... and when I walked out the door...my heart was breaking for them.
So many lives changed forever in an instant.
Yes, there's a lesson here... but this post is just about these two young women.
By all accounts, as close as twins... but now separated from each other forever.

26 year old driver from the Bronx is in police custody right now.
He's suspected of driving the wrong way thru Time Square-mowing down pedestrians.

We have a team of ABC7NY reporters on the scene... we'll keep you updated - on air, on line and on social media.
